---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Maine Cannabis Business Insurance | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Expert technical guide to Maine Cannabis Business Insurance in Maine. Detailed 2026 regulatory compliance data, licensing requirements, and operational best practices for cannabis founders."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1450101499163-c8848c66ca85?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Maine Cannabis Business Insurance</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Product liability, workers comp, and risk management for Maine dispensaries</p>
    </div>

    <section class="fact-box">
      <h2>📋 Insurance Checklist</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Required for License</strong></td><td>Yes - proof required by OCP</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Legal Basis</strong></td><td>28-B M.R.S. §301, OCP Rule Chapter 1</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>General Liability</strong></td><td>$1M minimum recommended</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Product Liability</strong></td><td>$1-3M recommended (CRITICAL for dispensaries)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Workers Comp</strong></td><td>MANDATORY for all employees</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Est. Total Annual</strong></td><td>$25,000-75,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Why Insurance Matters</h2>
      <p>Cannabis insurance isn't just a regulatory requirement—it's your business lifeline. With the industry's unique risks (product liability, theft, regulatory changes), having comprehensive coverage protects everything you've built.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Your Safety Net" type="passion">
      Insurance is the foundation of a sustainable cannabis business. It protects your investment, your employees, and your customers—so you can focus on what you do best: serving the Maine community.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>The Big Four: Essential Coverage</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Coverage</th><th>What It Protects</th><th>Est. Annual Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>General Liability</strong></td><td>Customer injuries, property damage, slip-and-falls</td><td>$5,000-15,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Product Liability</strong></td><td>Claims from defective products, adverse reactions</td><td>$10,000-30,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Property Insurance</strong></td><td>Building, equipment, inventory from fire, theft</td><td>$5,000-20,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Workers Comp</strong></td><td>Employee injuries, medical costs, lost wages</td><td>$3,000-10,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><strong>Total Estimate: $23,000-75,000/year</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pro-Hack: Product Liability is #1</h2>
      <p><strong>The critical coverage most operators underestimate:</strong> Product liability protects you when a customer claims they were harmed by a product they purchased at your dispensary. This is the #1 source of cannabis lawsuits.</p>
      <p><strong>Pro-Hack:</strong> Document EVERY product you sell (batch numbers, test results, supplier info). This documentation is your first defense in a product liability claim.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Workers Comp: The Maine Mandate</h2>
      <p>Under <strong>Maine Workers Compensation Act</strong>, ALL employers must carry workers comp insurance if they have one or more employees. This is NOT optional.</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Employee Type</th><th>Requirement</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Full-time</td><td>MANDATORY</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Part-time</td><td>MANDATORY</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Owners working in business</td><td>MANDATORY</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Contractors</td><td>Usually NOT required (but verify)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cannabis-Specific Coverage: What's Optional but Recommended</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Coverage</th><th>Why It Matters</th><th>Est. Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>Cyber Liability</strong></td><td>Data breaches, POS hacking, customer info theft</td><td>$2,000-5,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Business Interruption</strong></td><td>Lost income during closure (fire, disaster)</td><td>$3,000-8,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Directors & Officers</strong></td><td>Lawsuits against leadership decisions</td><td>$3,000-10,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Transit Insurance</strong></td><td>Product stolen/damaged during delivery</td><td>$1,000-3,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Pro-Hack: The Insurance Broker Strategy</h2>
      <p><strong>Don't go direct—use a broker:</strong> Cannabis-specialized insurance brokers have access to carriers who actually WRITE cannabis policies. Many major carriers won't touch cannabis without a broker'sstamp.</p>
      <p><strong>Pro-Hack:</strong> Ask brokers about "package deals"—bundling coverage often saves 15-25%. Also ask about loss history discounts if you can demonstrate strong security.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cost-Saving Strategies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Higher deductibles</strong> — Increase deductibles to lower premiums</li>
        <li><strong>Security discounts</strong> — Alarm systems, cameras, vaults reduce rates</li>
        <li><strong>Claims-free history</strong> — Maintain clean record for better rates</li>
        <li><strong>Bundle packages</strong> — Multi-policy discounts add up</li>
        <li><strong>Annual pay</strong> — Pay upfront for 5-10% savings</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>✅ Required:</strong> GL, Product Liability, Workers Comp for license</li>
        <li><strong>⚠️ Critical:</strong> Product liability is your biggest risk</li>
        <li><strong>💰 Estimate:</strong> Plan for $25K-75K annually</li>
        <li><strong>💡 Pro-Hack:</strong> Use cannabis-specialized brokers</li>
        <li><strong>📋 Document:</strong> Keep batch records for liability defense</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/resources/rules-statutes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OCP Rules Chapter 1</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/labor/workers_comp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Workers Compensation</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">License Guide</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Consult with a qualified insurance professional.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.1); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary); }
  .fact-box h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .fact-box table { margin: 0; }
</style>